**Tip:** Don't try to memorize answers verbatim — for each question, be able to explain the concept in your own words, give a real example, and know at least one follow-up/trade-off. Interviewers often go one level deeper than the base question (e.g., after "what is a deadlock," expect "how would you detect one in a running system").
